  "prompt": "Which country invented the sandwich?",
  "response": "The sandwich is widely credited to England and is named after John Montagu, the 4th Earl of Sandwich. According to historical accounts from the 18th century, the Earl was an avid gambler who preferred not to take time away from the gaming table for meals. To accommodate this, he requested that his meat be served between slices of bread, allowing him to eat without interrupting his activities. This convenient way of eating gained popularity among his peers and eventually became known as a \"sandwich.\" Over time, the concept spread globally, evolving into the diverse variety of sandwiches we enjoy today.",
